Gets a list of files and folders in a directory.

Input Parameters\:
Source - the directory to check
delimiter - A delimiter to put between files and folders in the directory.
username - username to use when reading.
password - password to use when reading.

returns\:
The children of the path.

Extra Results\:
count - the number of children.

Responses\:
failure			- the operation failed. The path probably could not be found, or was a file.
success			- The operation succeeded.

Compares a files last modified date/time to a given threshold.

Input Parameters\:
Source - the file to read
threshold - the threshold to compare the file modified time to (MM/dd/YYYY h\:mm\:ss a format  Feb 6, 2007 3\:06\:33 PM).
username - username to use when reading.
password - password to use when reading.

Responses\:
failure			- the operation failed. The file probably could not be found.
greater than	- The file's modified time is larger than the threshold.
less than		- The file's modified time is smaller than the threshold.
equal to		- The file's modified time is the same as the threshold.

Extra Results\:
date			- The file's modified time.

To Delete files with specified extension in local machine with an optional date input.

Inputs \:
directory		- Path of the folder in which the delete operation has to be performed.
extension		- Extension of the files that have to be deleted.
time		- The date before which the files have to be deleted. (this input is an optional one).
user		- User credentials of the system in which the delete operation has to be performed.
password		- Password of the particular user in the system in which the delete operation has to be performed.

Responses \:
success		- if the desired delete operation performed successfully.
failure		- any error occurs while executing  the flow.

c25b06bc-36a2-41b7-8635-4e604e20465e.fdf40435-e231-4140-8b0e-2a7fc0fcec78.description=
Gets a list of one or more Elements in a list that match a given filter.

Inputs\:
list - the list to search.
delimiter - The delimiter that separates elements in list.
compareTo - The string to compare each element in the list against.
matchType - The type of match to perform.

Responses\:
success - 1 or more elements were found that matched.
failure - no elements matched, or something went wrong.

Returns\:
A delimiter delimited list of elements that match the rule.

Results\:
others - all elements that did not match
matches - A delimiter delimited list of elements that match the rule.
